# Career-Ops

This project uses the [career-ops](https://github.com/santifer/career-ops) plugin.
Run `/career-ops` to see all commands or paste a job URL to start evaluating.

## Data Contract (CRITICAL)

**User layer — NEVER auto-update:**
`cv.md`, `config/profile.yml`, `config/_profile.md`, `article-digest.md`, `portals.yml`, `data/*`, `reports/*`, `output/*`, `interview-prep/*`

**System layer — safe to update:**
`modes/`, `*.mjs` scripts, `templates/*`, `batch/*` (non-data)

When the user customizes archetypes, narrative, negotiation scripts, or scoring weights: write to `config/_profile.md` or `config/profile.yml`. NEVER edit `modes/_shared.md` for user-specific content.

## Tracker Integrity

- NEVER add new rows directly to `data/applications.md`
- Write TSV to `batch/tracker-additions/{num}-{slug}.tsv` → run `node merge-tracker.mjs`
- YES: update status/notes of existing rows in `applications.md` directly

## Canonical States

`Evaluated` | `Applied` | `Responded` | `Interview` | `Offer` | `Rejected` | `Discarded` | `SKIP`

Rules: no bold, no dates, no extra text in the status field.

## Ethics

- NEVER submit an application without the user reviewing it first
- Score below 4.0/5 → recommend against applying
- Quality over quantity — 5 targeted applications beat 50 generic ones
